// Adversarial: BumpWhiff fires a DamageBoost(2.5) via Once (consumed on first whiff)
// and a Shockwave on every whiff. Dense layout maximises bolt-breaker contact events,
// and chaos 0.5 produces a natural mix of successful bumps and mistimed whiffs.
// The adversarial risk: if the BumpWhiff bridge evaluates the When node more than once
// per whiff event (e.g., due to double-read of BumpWhiffed), DamageBoost stacks
// silently and the Shockwave spawns duplicate rings that are never cleaned up.
// If BumpWhiff fires even when no bump input was registered, the Once is consumed
// prematurely and the effect is lost. NoEntityLeaks detects leaked Shockwave ring
// entities that fail to expand and despawn. BoltSpeedAccurate catches indirect
// speed corruption from a runaway DamageBoost multiplier. NoNaN guards against
// uninitialized velocity in spawned Shockwave entities. 5000 frames at moderate
// chaos ensures many whiff events without exhausting the node prematurely.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.5)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 2311,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: AllBolts, then: [
            When(trigger: BumpWhiff, then: [
                Once([
                    Do(DamageBoost(2.5)),
                ]),
                Do(Shockwave(base_range: 50.0, range_per_level: 0.0, stacks: 1, speed: 200.0)),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
